al History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Taylor-Billy/Taylor_Billy_Transcript.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Hinton Milt", "relation": "has met", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "All the great black entertainers of that era, Roland Hayes, [Unintelligible}, Marion Anderson, they were all there... It‟s the man from New York... I‟ll never forget it because it was first time to play in anything like that with Roland Hayes there and all these people.", "doc_title": "Hinton Milt — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Hinton-Milt/Milt_Hinton_Interview_Transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Mahalia Jackson", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "I didn't get a chance to hear, uh, the great singers like Roland Hayes... until I came to Chicago up north.", "doc_title": "Mahalia Jackson Interview, 1955-07-26", "collection": "tulane", "url": "https://library.search.tulane.edu/permalink/01TUL_INST/4h6sc4/alma9945592977206326"}, {"speaker": "Jimmy Jones", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "people like maybe Roland Hayes or Paul Robeson. That was a big thing in those days, you know?", "doc_title": "69537_Jimmy Jones oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/69537/"}, {"speaker": "J. C. Higginbotham", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "[INTERVIEWER] What about Roland Hayes? [INTERVIEWER] Good, in my opinion.", "doc_title": "67247_J.C. Higginbotham oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67247/"}]}